# Fluff Date: 2026-02-26 19:50:04
<overview>
<p>The Leviathan II Battleship is the most powerful warship class ever fielded by Clan Ghost Bear and its successor state, the Rasalhague Dominion. Bearing the same two million four hundred thousand ton displacement as the Leviathan Heavy Transport from which it evolved, the class represents the fulfillment of an ambition first conceived decades earlier to construct a vessel surpassing the McKenna in both size and firepower. Built and converted at the Alshain Naval Yards, the class emerged from a complex development history in which the original Leviathan battleship design was modified through an intermediate transport configuration before finally achieving its intended combat role. The resulting design differs from the never-built original Leviathan specifications but incorporates lessons learned during the transport phase alongside advances in Clan weapons technology, making the Leviathan II the undisputed centerpiece of the Dominion's strategic naval deterrent.</p>
</overview>

<capabilities>
<p>The Leviathan II mounts an extraordinarily dense weapons suite across all firing arcs. The nose section carries heavy naval Gauss rifles, naval autocannons, seven medium naval particle projector cannons, twelve naval laser fifty-fives, and an AR-10 capital missile launcher. Extensive arrays of conventional Clan weapons including extended-range lasers, pulse lasers, Gauss rifles, and ATM-12 batteries provide layered defense against fighters and smaller craft. The broadside arcs concentrate the heaviest sustained firepower, with medium naval Gauss rifles backed by twenty-four naval laser fifty-fives per side and full batteries of extended-range PPCs, pulse lasers, and LRM-20 launchers with Artemis IV guidance. Anti-missile systems and Streak SRM-6 launchers protect the vessel from approaching ordnance at all angles.</p><p>The vessel maintains eight docking collars for DropShips and two massive fighter bays housing a combined three hundred aerospace fighters, giving the class organic carrier capability unmatched outside dedicated carrier designs. Nine thousand five hundred double heat sinks manage the staggering thermal output of the weapons suite. Structural integrity of one hundred fifty reflects the massively reinforced hull construction, while Ferro-Carbide armor provides outstanding protection across all arcs. A lithium-fusion battery permits consecutive hyperspace jumps, and a mobile HPG maintains independent interstellar communications. The one notable limitation is the vessel's modest thrust profile, a trade-off imposed by the enormous mass that must be accelerated.</p>
</capabilities>

<deployment>
<p>The CGB Rasalhague was the third Leviathan-class vessel and the only one built directly to the Leviathan II battleship specifications. Constructed at the Alshain Naval Yards, the vessel's progress was disrupted in 3064 when the Draconis Combine's Alshain Avengers attacked the shipyard, an incident that helped trigger the broader Combine-Ghost Bear War. Further delays followed in May 3067 when Clan Nova Cat launched a Trial of Retribution, attempting to seize the incomplete hull. The resulting Naval Battle of Alshain lasted eight days and inflicted devastating losses on both sides, though the Ghost Bears retained possession. The Rasalhague finally launched in December 3069.</p><p>The vessel saw extensive Jihad service. At the Battle of Tukayyid in July 3070, the Rasalhague led a task force that swiftly knocked the Blakist McKenna-class Blake's Sword out of action, with the massive vessel reportedly shrugging off nuclear weapon impacts. At the Battle of Dyev in July 3076, the vessel engaged alongside the Nightlord-class Ursa Major and the Aegis-class Scabbard, destroying multiple Blakist warships before enduring a seven-hour counterassault. The Rasalhague subsequently served as part of Task Force EARTHBOUND during the liberation of Terra. As the sole Leviathan-class vessel to survive the Jihad, the Rasalhague remained the most powerful warship in the Rasalhague Dominion fleet. In December 3099, the vessel led a flotilla in the Bikini Atoll Raid, destroying Combine factory ships. During the Dominion Civil War, Star Admiral Tanya Bourjon declared the navy neutral, keeping the Rasalhague stationed at Alshain while maintaining open JumpShip traffic until the conflict's resolution.</p><p>The CGB Leviathan and CGB Great Bear, the first two vessels of the broader Leviathan program, were originally completed as heavy transports before being converted to the Leviathan II configuration at Alshain. Both served during the Jihad. The Leviathan supported operations at Kaus Borealis and Ascella before being lost at the Battle of Dieron on the twentieth of November 3077, when Blakist forces concentrated their fire on the massive battleship. The Great Bear was destroyed during Task Force CRONUS's assault on the Titan Yards near Terra, overwhelmed by a concealed Dragon's Breath Multiple Capital Missile Launch System.</p>
</deployment>

<history>
<p>The Leviathan II class emerged from the decades-long Leviathan program initiated in 3044 by Clan Ghost Bear. After the two original hulls were completed as armed transports for the Third Exodus in 3055, plans began to convert them to their intended battleship configuration. The extensive mid-construction transport modifications meant the resulting warships would differ from the original Leviathan battleship specifications, creating the distinct Leviathan II designation. Both converted vessels were operational by 3061.</p><p>Construction of a third vessel built directly to the Leviathan II design commenced at the Alshain Naval Yards in the early 3060s. The project faced repeated disruptions. A Draconis Combine attack on the shipyard in 3064 triggered the Combine-Ghost Bear War, and in May 3067, Clan Nova Cat launched a Trial of Retribution in an attempt to seize the incomplete hull. The eight-day Naval Battle of Alshain that followed inflicted devastating losses on both Clans, with the Ghost Bears losing several warships while retaining possession of the Leviathan II. The vessel finally launched in December 3069, entering service during one of the most turbulent periods in Inner Sphere history.</p><p>All three Leviathan II vessels saw extensive combat during the Jihad, proving the class to be an extraordinarily capable combatant. The vessels demonstrated the ability to absorb tremendous punishment, including nuclear weapon strikes, while delivering overwhelming firepower against even the largest opposing warships. However, the Jihad exacted a heavy toll. Two of the three vessels were destroyed during the final stages of Operation SCOUR, one lost in the liberation of Dieron and the other destroyed by a concealed weapons system during the assault on the Titan Yards near Terra.</p><p>The sole surviving vessel continued to serve as the most powerful warship in the Rasalhague Dominion's fleet throughout the post-Jihad era. The vessel's presence served as a powerful strategic deterrent, and it remained in active service through the ilClan period. No additional Leviathan II hulls were constructed, though the Alshain Naval Yards later began work on the successor Leviathan III design. The Leviathan II class stands as a testament to the ambition and determination of Clan Ghost Bear, a program that endured decades of setbacks before producing what many naval historians consider the most formidable warship class to serve in the Inner Sphere during the thirty-first century.</p>
</history>

